{
  "stem": "323.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right, the only thing I still want to say is after this accident and Erica's being killed, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I felt that I really didn't need this, on top of it, which, which is probably self-pity.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But on top of everything else, why did this have to happen to me, this-- you know, in addition to everything else.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] people gave me these books written-- 'What Happens When Bad Things Happen to Good People,' which is-- and then the rabbi came to my bed in the hospital and all that.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And really, all I wanted to do is be left alone and try to, you know, get over this.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But Jill, Andy and Harris-- this is my youngest grandson-- came to Massachusetts, stayed in the house with me, and stayed with me while I was there as well as-- some of my friends took weeks off from work and came to stay with me.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the ski club was 100% behind me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I never-- the hospital has never-- had never seen so many cards and so many flowers in the history of the hospital in Pittsfield, Massachusetts.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So it's-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it's, it can make one-- I feel good knowing that people do care.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it's something that I had to learn to live with.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And life goes on.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the best thing that ever happened to me is my children and now my grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have four grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And each one has-- they each had first a girl and then a boy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Jill has Dina and Harris.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And Dan has-- Dina is nine, Harris is five.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He just was five.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Dan has Lily and Jake.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Dan's wife, Ursula, is Catholic.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
